<br>
I am a young High Elf magician in her 3rd circle looking for a worldly mentor or friend to keep me out of trouble.<br>
<br>
I was born to noble parents in Felwithe, but have proven to be a pale comparison to them.  So I have struck out into the world to make my own path, and eventually prove myself worthy of my family name.<br>
<br>
The trouble is, I'm a bit slow.  It takes me longer to grasp magics that others learn so quickly.  While I'm far from ignorant, I am not as magically inclined as my family.  But I do make up for it with enthusiasm and willingness to experience new things.<br>
<br>
Perhaps there is someone out there who can help me, to offer advice or friendship.  And maybe in return I can enrich their life.  Or at least provide them with a never ending source of humorous anecdotes to share with their friends.<br>
<br>
<br>
OOC:  I'm a casual player, and therefore doesn't level fast.  Which brought me to my characters history and suitable personality that ties in with my playing habits.  I am NOT looking to be power-leveled or twinked.  My goal on Firiona Vie is to earn all my gains by completing quests (or by earning my own money to buy items in the bazaar).  I will never beg or ask for hand-me-downs.<br>
<br>
The help I request is strictly in the roleplay setting.  I'm looking for friends and people to group with, to help out with languages and to work on trade skills.<br>
<br>
~Peht<br>
High Elf Magician  |  3rd Circle  |  Firiona Vie<br>
