<br>
&quot;We have been looking for you Peth.&quot;-the wizardress starts to talk, sitting down on the grass. &quot;You have been looking for friends and mentors out there in the world. We are sorry it took us so long to seek you out, but the spirits we were consulting were... reluctant.&quot;-she glances at the shaman with a smile and continues &quot;I am Ennisser Arianrod, one of the family of The Ring of Mystic Souls and the trouble of being slow at was once mine. And it happens to all of us from time to time that we just do not visit Norrath, spending time at fruitless research and study. However our Family, which can be yours if such is your wish, understands that and supports all of its members- we just wait for our researches to go hunting with us again.&quot; She smiles at Peth.<br>
<br>
&quot;If you are looking for a family then I dare say you can't find no better in Norrath. If you are looking for a mentor- we have Zalrenea the Mage, gifted with the ability to be a best mentor and friend one can ever have. And there is another mage in our ranks who is only in her 13th circle- I am sure you'll have stories to share. And as you seem to be particularly interested in questing for everything Norrath has for you to offer- well, I brought Aelros, our Guild Shaman and the greatest quester in NOrrath. Everything he owns he gained by questing, and questing is what he most enjoys about Norrath. He is also eager to share his knowledge and help anyone ready and willing to quest- as our whole family is.&quot; Ennisser stands up. &quot;Now I'd leave you two and get me some bat wings- I need those badly. I will be right back and I really hope you decide to join me and Aelros on our way back home.&quot;<br>
<br>
